1
00:00:06,160 --> 00:00:08,200
It smells like someone died in the car.

2
00:00:08,280 --> 00:00:10,160
Do you think someone died here?

3
00:00:10,240 --> 00:00:13,240
Mom, she’s scaring me.
-No, nobody's dead, girls,

4
00:00:13,320 --> 00:00:14,560
Dude, that’s a rotten apple.

5
00:00:15,240 --> 00:00:16,880
Honey, maybe we should save this gift for later?

6
00:00:16,960 --> 00:00:19,160
No, no, honey, we’re giving
my mom what I bought,

7
00:00:19,240 --> 00:00:20,680
What you bought, leave it in the trunk.

8
00:00:20,760 --> 00:00:22,880
You haven’t even seen her.
-Okay, no need.

9
00:00:23,440 --> 00:00:24,960
Why are we leaving so early?

10
00:00:25,040 --> 00:00:26,760
Because Grandma is celebrating her 60th birthday today.

11
00:00:26,880 --> 00:00:28,600
How old is she?
-63.

12
00:00:34,760 --> 00:00:37,400
Look at me, look at me and...

13
00:00:46,720 --> 00:00:49,320
And let’s meet the new couple of contestants.

14
00:00:49,400 --> 00:00:51,040
Here come Rachel and Silvan,

15
00:00:51,360 --> 00:00:54,040
parents of five and grandparents to...

16
00:00:54,520 --> 00:00:55,920
I’m intentionally not saying how many

17
00:00:56,000 --> 00:00:59,680
so the audience won’t go “knock on wood”
and jinx the whole studio.

18
00:01:00,560 --> 00:01:02,440
Rachel and Silvan Hasson.

19
00:01:02,680 --> 00:01:03,800
There you go, that’s all we recorded.

20
00:01:04,440 --> 00:01:05,440
Since when do you have this receiver?

21
00:01:06,000 --> 00:01:07,240
They did this deal because of Meirav

22
00:01:07,320 --> 00:01:09,320
that includes internet, phone, and the Tami 4

23
00:01:09,440 --> 00:01:10,480
and they also got this receiver.

24
00:01:10,960 --> 00:01:14,080
What, and let’s say I already had this receiver,
then what, how could I record?

25
00:01:14,200 --> 00:01:16,800
I was filming, it was live.

26
00:01:16,880 --> 00:01:20,040
So what, you don’t have to be home,
you can schedule a recording on the receiver.

27
00:01:20,440 --> 00:01:21,920
No, no, no, it’s a new receiver,

28
00:01:22,040 --> 00:01:25,560
I want to learn more about how to program it.

29
00:01:25,640 --> 00:01:27,800
There’s nothing to program here, Dad, it’s not like the VCR.

30
00:01:28,920 --> 00:01:30,840
So how does it record?
-What does it record?

31
00:01:31,120 --> 00:01:33,800
What recorder? There’s no recording,
it saves it to the hard drive.

32
00:01:35,040 --> 00:01:38,120
So where’s the disk that has the show?

33
00:01:39,200 --> 00:01:40,120
Inside the receiver.

34
00:01:41,800 --> 00:01:45,240
And how do you get the disk out after?
-From the receiver.

35
00:01:45,720 --> 00:01:48,520
With a VCR, when you recorded something
you knew you were recording.

36
00:01:49,800 --> 00:01:53,120
You could plan everything with the remote, you know?

37
00:01:53,200 --> 00:01:55,880
You’d set the clock,

38
00:01:56,120 --> 00:01:58,760
choose the time you want
to watch the show,

39
00:01:58,920 --> 00:02:01,520
hit record...

40
00:02:02,000 --> 00:02:04,160
Yeah, Dad, and how long has the VCR been broken?

41
00:02:05,640 --> 00:02:07,040
It’s expensive, you don’t know how much it is,

42
00:02:07,240 --> 00:02:11,800
there’s no technician in the country who knows how to fix
those VCRs, it’s not...

43
00:02:13,240 --> 00:02:17,760
It’s a VCR with four heads,

44
00:02:19,480 --> 00:02:20,400
four heads.

45
00:02:21,240 --> 00:02:24,320
You’d put the tape in

46
00:02:24,920 --> 00:02:29,680
and you’d feel someone inside
accepting it and not dodging.

47
00:02:29,760 --> 00:02:31,800
Yeah, there was a little slot like that...

48
00:02:32,480 --> 00:02:36,600
pulling the tape in and the door would close,

49
00:02:36,920 --> 00:02:41,320
and then you’d hear four heads starting to rev up,

50
00:02:42,080 --> 00:02:43,080
like some jumbo jet.

51
00:02:46,480 --> 00:02:50,360
And if it broke down, you could
open a parachute that was inside the VCR

52
00:02:50,440 --> 00:02:51,440
that would save it.

53
00:02:54,320 --> 00:02:55,720
Laugh, laugh.

54
00:02:56,240 --> 00:02:59,360
Say, did Rachel ask Alon and Manny
to bring the rest of the show?

55
00:02:59,440 --> 00:03:01,440
Yeah, Manny has a DVD burner,

56
00:03:01,880 --> 00:03:03,680
he’ll download it, okay?

57
00:03:03,800 --> 00:03:06,400
They’ll record it on a disk, don’t worry.

58
00:03:11,080 --> 00:03:14,960
Mom, happy birthday.
-Hey, sweetie, thank you, thank you.

59
00:03:15,040 --> 00:03:17,600
And I’m so sorry
I didn’t manage to bring you anything yet.

60
00:03:17,680 --> 00:03:21,600
It’s okay, it’s really not important, I don’t need gifts.

61
00:03:21,800 --> 00:03:23,480
My gift for you.

62
00:03:23,600 --> 00:03:26,440
Yeah, but it was important to me
to bring you something small and meaningful.

63
00:03:26,920 --> 00:03:29,520
No, it’s really not important, not small or meaningful, really.

64
00:03:29,600 --> 00:03:30,640
No, it is important.

65
00:03:30,720 --> 00:03:33,520
I was already on my way to Azrieli,
and you won’t believe the crazy traffic,

66
00:03:33,600 --> 00:03:35,160
we moved one meter, then went back two,

67
00:03:35,280 --> 00:03:38,080
and tons of ambulances, police, fire trucks.

68
00:03:38,160 --> 00:03:42,120
In the end, it turned out to be
some suspicious package on Maza Street.

69
00:03:42,960 --> 00:03:44,120
I love you.

70
00:03:44,200 --> 00:03:47,040
Okay, I’m going to order you
something online and get dressed.

71
00:03:49,800 --> 00:03:52,160
Shabbat Shalom.

72
00:03:52,920 --> 00:03:54,520
Shabbat Shalom.
-Shabbat Shalom.

73
00:03:54,720 --> 00:03:56,280
Shabbat Shalom.

74
00:03:57,000 --> 00:03:58,760
Shabbat Shalom, Shabbat Shalom.

75
00:03:58,960 --> 00:04:01,560
Wow, Dad, you were amazing on TV.

76
00:04:01,960 --> 00:04:04,080
Yeah, yeah, there was this photographer

77
00:04:04,160 --> 00:04:05,440
who told me that.
-Nice.

78
00:04:05,520 --> 00:04:06,960
Where’s Shai?

79
00:04:07,040 --> 00:04:09,920
He had a little mishap with a strudel in the car.
-Hope it’s not too bad.

80
00:04:10,400 --> 00:04:14,200
Shabbat Shalom.
-Shabbat Shalom, Shayka.

81
00:04:14,280 --> 00:04:15,440
What’s this, a gift for Rachel?

82
00:04:17,200 --> 00:04:18,880
She’s tough when it comes to gifts, huh?

83
00:04:19,000 --> 00:04:20,399
Where’s Mom?
-In the kitchen.

84
00:04:20,480 --> 00:04:21,600
Shai, come here for a sec.

85
00:04:23,760 --> 00:04:25,680
This isn’t the gift I was hoping for.
-Not really.

86
00:04:25,760 --> 00:04:28,080
Why did you bring this poster here
after we agreed not to?

87
00:04:28,160 --> 00:04:29,760
You agreed, I didn’t.

88
00:04:29,840 --> 00:04:31,840
Okay, Shai, listen,
don’t you dare leave this here, okay?

89
00:04:32,000 --> 00:04:34,040
Jump to the bedroom and think of a good excuse

90
00:04:34,520 --> 00:04:35,560
and about mold.

91
00:04:36,320 --> 00:04:37,160
I’ll be right back.

92
00:04:38,880 --> 00:04:40,480
Congratulations.

93
00:04:40,680 --> 00:04:42,800
Thanks, thank you, my sweet.

94
00:04:43,760 --> 00:04:44,640
Thank you very much.

95
00:04:44,720 --> 00:04:46,480
Congratulations.
-Thanks, beautiful, thank you.

96
00:04:46,560 --> 00:04:49,080
Go to Shachar, dolls. Congratulations, Mom.
-Thank you, thank you.

97
00:04:50,280 --> 00:04:51,120
Thank you.

98
00:04:51,200 --> 00:04:53,480
I don’t understand why you insist
on working so hard on your birthday.

99
00:04:53,560 --> 00:04:55,520
Seriously, why are you making such a big deal
about my birthday,

100
00:04:55,600 --> 00:04:58,320
I’d rather celebrate all the other days of the year.

101
00:04:58,400 --> 00:04:59,960
Okay, Mom. Stop it, come on, times have changed,

102
00:05:00,360 --> 00:05:02,280
today’s sixties are like the fifties back then.

103
00:05:03,400 --> 00:05:04,240
Where’s Meirav?

104
00:05:04,480 --> 00:05:07,120
She’s probably stuck in traffic at the Google entrance.

105
00:05:08,480 --> 00:05:12,160
Shabbat Shalom.
-Shabbat Shalom, Shabbat Shalom.

106
00:05:12,560 --> 00:05:15,240
Shabbat Shalom.
-Shabbat Shalom.

107
00:05:15,800 --> 00:05:17,080
Riki Ben Sharivan, did you bring the disc?

108
00:05:17,200 --> 00:05:18,640
We did. Why, haven’t you seen it yet?

109
00:05:18,800 --> 00:05:20,320
We’ve seen it, the main stars haven’t.

110
00:05:20,960 --> 00:05:23,040
They were in the studio, didn’t know
how to record with the new converter.

111
00:05:23,120 --> 00:05:24,240
Moshe, be quiet.

112
00:05:24,720 --> 00:05:26,880
Okay, the disc is here, everyone’s here,
can we start the screening?

113
00:05:28,480 --> 00:05:29,440
Give me the...

114
00:05:30,960 --> 00:05:34,160
Mom, sit down, Meirav, come on, we want to start.

115
00:05:34,480 --> 00:05:36,800
Silvan, come on, run through
all the contestants from the show,

116
00:05:36,880 --> 00:05:39,480
we don’t have to watch everything,
just put on your part, I’m hungry.

117
00:05:40,360 --> 00:05:41,680
Don’t stand over me, okay?

118
00:05:42,760 --> 00:05:43,600
This is the remote for the video.

119
00:05:47,720 --> 00:05:48,960
Are you going to stand over me for a long time?

120
00:05:49,720 --> 00:05:50,800
Sit down.

121
00:05:52,560 --> 00:05:55,120
Why are the signs in plastic?
-Because it keeps them fresh.

122
00:05:57,880 --> 00:06:00,120
Please. Thanks.

123
00:06:02,920 --> 00:06:03,960
Here, I'm running it.

124
00:06:04,040 --> 00:06:05,880
You know if you press it again
it’ll run faster?

125
00:06:08,880 --> 00:06:10,000
Times four.

126
00:06:10,640 --> 00:06:12,080
So that’s times four in fast mode.

127
00:06:12,280 --> 00:06:14,600
If you press it again, it’s times 16.

128
00:06:17,320 --> 00:06:18,280
Times 30.

129
00:06:19,040 --> 00:06:22,480
I don’t get it, why is it times 30 and not times 32?

130
00:06:22,640 --> 00:06:24,960
Stop, stop, stop, rewind, rewind.

131
00:06:25,720 --> 00:06:26,920
Why did you hit "stop"?

132
00:06:27,000 --> 00:06:29,560
Now we have to run everything from the start,
you should’ve pressed "play."

133
00:06:29,640 --> 00:06:30,720
Okay, okay,

134
00:06:30,800 --> 00:06:33,360
I can run it, I have times 30 here,

135
00:06:33,440 --> 00:06:38,480
What’s wrong with you? Come on, run it, run it, run it.

136
00:06:38,560 --> 00:06:39,480
Stop!

137
00:06:40,160 --> 00:06:41,160
No...

138
00:06:45,400 --> 00:06:46,480
I see she’s twitching a bit

139
00:06:46,560 --> 00:06:47,960
and I’m going downstairs to get your gift from the car.

140
00:06:48,120 --> 00:06:50,200
But at least look at this one.
-Okay, fine, just quick.

141
00:06:50,320 --> 00:06:52,040
Because they want to start the episode screening.

142
00:06:52,640 --> 00:06:54,040
It’s not cheap either, it costs 159 shekels.

143
00:06:54,120 --> 00:06:56,720
What? You paid 160?
-That’s its price,

144
00:06:56,800 --> 00:06:58,520
they gave me a discount because they just opened the business,

145
00:06:58,600 --> 00:07:00,280
they based their new software on me.
-How much?

146
00:07:00,360 --> 00:07:02,800
I was the first one so...
-How much?

147
00:07:06,640 --> 00:07:09,000
Wow, that’s really nice.
-See?

148
00:07:09,160 --> 00:07:11,560
What, like, you designed this?
-Of course you get it?

149
00:07:11,800 --> 00:07:13,640
That’s exactly why they invented this software,

150
00:07:13,720 --> 00:07:16,720
you just input all the details into the computer,
and it edits it for you automatically

151
00:07:16,800 --> 00:07:18,760
with pictures and colors and all that...

152
00:07:18,840 --> 00:07:20,440
They print it on high-quality canvas.

153
00:07:20,520 --> 00:07:21,400
See? Canvas.

154
00:07:22,640 --> 00:07:23,800
No, that’s really a nice choice.

155
00:07:24,680 --> 00:07:26,280
So?
-So go down to the car and bring my gift.

156
00:07:26,360 --> 00:07:27,680
Why?
-Why? Just because.

157
00:07:27,760 --> 00:07:30,800
Because it seems to me, I don’t know how or why
that this gift will bring me disaster.

158
00:07:30,880 --> 00:07:32,080
How did you get to disaster? It’s a gift.

159
00:07:32,560 --> 00:07:34,360
Honey, listen for a second, you can’t go wrong with bedding.

160
00:07:35,080 --> 00:07:36,080
I’ll make you a deal, okay?

161
00:07:36,240 --> 00:07:37,560
Let’s ask everyone what they think about it

162
00:07:37,760 --> 00:07:39,480
if they like it, then we’ll keep the bedding for ourselves,

163
00:07:39,560 --> 00:07:40,800
treat yourself a bit, what’s the harm?

164
00:07:42,360 --> 00:07:43,200
Okay, fine,

165
00:07:43,360 --> 00:07:45,560
it’s only because I hate you.
-I hate you too, honey.

166
00:07:46,120 --> 00:07:47,160
Sorry.

167
00:07:47,400 --> 00:07:49,160
I’m just looking for a place to put it down.

168
00:07:49,240 --> 00:07:50,480
Sure, sure.
-Thanks.

169
00:07:53,200 --> 00:07:56,280
Rachel and Silvan Hasson, how many weeks have you been married?

170
00:07:57,000 --> 00:07:57,880
Too few.

171
00:07:58,160 --> 00:08:00,120
If you could, you’d marry her first.

172
00:08:03,040 --> 00:08:04,680
I’d marry him again too.

173
00:08:04,760 --> 00:08:07,160
But what do I need, I’m at the peak of happiness.

174
00:08:08,720 --> 00:08:12,160
So let’s just settle on saying
you’re a long-time loving couple

175
00:08:12,440 --> 00:08:14,520
back when there was a hole in the TV.

176
00:08:14,640 --> 00:08:17,880
No, no, no, there wasn’t a hole in the TV.

177
00:08:18,200 --> 00:08:21,920
But we used to watch a lot
on three and six on Jordan.

178
00:08:22,000 --> 00:08:24,920
Well, with your permission
we’ll now go to 17 short commercials

179
00:08:25,280 --> 00:08:26,280
and we’ll be right back.

180
00:08:26,440 --> 00:08:29,400
17 commercials and a few promos and we’ll be back shortly.

181
00:08:29,480 --> 00:08:31,000
How nice.

182
00:08:31,080 --> 00:08:32,679
Dad, did you see the show? Really.

183
00:08:33,039 --> 00:08:34,799
What, it was so beautiful, what you said.

184
00:08:35,240 --> 00:08:38,960
Did you see that? They gave me a big round of applause!

185
00:08:39,880 --> 00:08:42,039
I didn’t remember that from the filming, really.

186
00:08:42,120 --> 00:08:44,840
Mom, where are you going?
-I need to check something in the kitchen.

187
00:08:45,000 --> 00:08:46,040
Call me when the commercials are over.

188
00:08:46,120 --> 00:08:47,960
No, no, no, what commercials? Fast forward, fast forward,

189
00:08:48,040 --> 00:08:50,080
Don’t waste time, Silvan.
-Okay, okay.

190
00:08:50,200 --> 00:08:52,880
You guys were really good, Silvan, really
Dad was sure you’d take the multi.

191
00:08:52,960 --> 00:08:53,840
Thanks.

192
00:08:53,920 --> 00:08:56,040
Dad, do you want me to fast forward from the device?

193
00:08:56,120 --> 00:08:59,000
No, I don’t want to, I can fast forward myself, okay?

194
00:08:59,640 --> 00:09:00,680
No, Dad, you’re on "pause."

195
00:09:01,800 --> 00:09:04,040
How is this under pressure?
-Look, you pressed both lines.

196
00:09:04,120 --> 00:09:05,960
Wow, I’m starving.
-Dad, just fast forward already.

197
00:09:06,040 --> 00:09:07,240
I’m fast forwarding, I’m fast forwarding.

198
00:09:07,880 --> 00:09:09,760
This is teaching me what pause means.

199
00:09:10,680 --> 00:09:13,680
Kid, do you know how many pauses
I’ve pressed in my life?

200
00:09:14,320 --> 00:09:15,520
Pause is teaching me.

201
00:09:15,600 --> 00:09:17,440
Mom, is everything okay?
-Yeah, everything’s fine.

202
00:09:18,400 --> 00:09:21,200
You’re filming the show.
-Yeah, for Gili.

203
00:09:21,320 --> 00:09:23,760
No, no, no, not just for Gili, you’re filming the show.

204
00:09:24,040 --> 00:09:26,200
It’s just that "bad TV adds five pounds."

205
00:09:26,280 --> 00:09:27,600
And ages you by ten weeks.

206
00:09:28,400 --> 00:09:29,680
Or the other way around.
-Yeah.

207
00:09:29,760 --> 00:09:32,400
It’s also known that Lovdon and Kirshenbaum are 48.

208
00:09:32,800 --> 00:09:34,560
Yoni Levy isn’t really pretty in real life.

209
00:09:34,640 --> 00:09:36,760
And Riva’s husband isn’t doing so well.

210
00:09:37,880 --> 00:09:38,920
Wipe your hands.

211
00:09:39,560 --> 00:09:42,280
Hey, is that picture your gift for Rachel?

212
00:09:43,680 --> 00:09:44,680
It looks cute.

213
00:09:44,760 --> 00:09:48,080
Yeah, Dad always makes me buy
bedding or pots.

214
00:09:48,400 --> 00:09:49,920
Sit down, come listen for a sec.
-Just a second, hold on.

215
00:09:50,000 --> 00:09:51,760
Orna, come here for a minute.
-Where to?

216
00:09:51,840 --> 00:09:52,720
You come too.

217
00:09:52,800 --> 00:09:55,320
Come, listen, listen for a second.
-In a minute, just a second.

218
00:09:55,400 --> 00:09:56,800
What, again with the stop now?

219
00:09:56,880 --> 00:09:59,440
Okay, keep watching,
we’ll be right there, what’s the rush?

220
00:10:00,320 --> 00:10:02,760
Hey, why aren’t you recording the shows
on the hard disk of the box?

221
00:10:03,160 --> 00:10:04,040
Quiet.

222
00:10:04,120 --> 00:10:06,360
Come on, Moshe, where’s the triangle now?

223
00:10:08,320 --> 00:10:11,960
Wow, did you know that both Marilyn Monroe
and Anne Frank were born under Mom’s sign?

224
00:10:12,440 --> 00:10:15,160
I wouldn’t call it luck, but it turns out.

225
00:10:15,720 --> 00:10:18,000
It’s designed really beautifully, is this your husband’s work?

226
00:10:18,080 --> 00:10:20,520
It’s amazing. What do you think, is it too dangerous?

227
00:10:21,520 --> 00:10:23,560
No... I know.

228
00:10:24,560 --> 00:10:26,040
On the face of it, it looks fine

229
00:10:26,520 --> 00:10:27,400
but there’s always a risk.

230
00:10:28,920 --> 00:10:30,000
I’m scared.

231
00:10:30,960 --> 00:10:34,600
Thanks for coming back to us,
we’re with the wonderful couple Rachel and Silvan Hasson.

232
00:10:34,720 --> 00:10:36,480
Are you ready?
-Yeah, yeah.

233
00:10:36,560 --> 00:10:38,680
Just let’s not waste our help too quickly.

234
00:10:38,760 --> 00:10:39,640
There’s no help here.

235
00:10:40,880 --> 00:10:43,640
The questions are between gods or aliens.

236
00:10:44,320 --> 00:10:46,840
I don’t know about aliens, do you know anything?

237
00:10:47,840 --> 00:10:49,400
Gods.
-Gods.

238
00:10:49,480 --> 00:10:50,520
Gods, okay.
-Gods.

239
00:10:50,640 --> 00:10:52,560
Pay attention, the answers are...
-Yeah.

